    <!--Minerals Council at Joburg Indaba-1-->
    <div class="item">
        <div class="row no-gutters b-mainpic banner-hm-joburg-indaba-2020">
            <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12 col-md-9 col-lg-7 b-content pull-right">
                <div class="b-contentblock">
                    <div class="row">
                        <h2>Minerals Council at Joburg Indaba</h2>
                        <h3>7-8 October 2020 <span>ONLINE EDITION</span></h3>
                        <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12 col-md-6 nopad-l">
                            <p class="lead">Minerals Council President, Mxolisi Mgojo and CEO, Roger Baxter today participated in Joburg Indaba 2020</p>
                            <p>
                                <strong>Roger Baxter</strong> participated in a panel discussion titled: What is the outlook for the world economy, commodity markets and the global industry? How should the South African economy and mining
                                industry be reset?
                            </p>
                            <p>In his keynote address <strong>Mxolisi Mgojo</strong> reflected on the mining industry’s response to COVID-19 and the lessons learned.</p>
                            <a class="btn btn-default" href="/downloads/send/19-latest/1247-health-and-safety-industry-response-to-covid-19" rel="external">Presentation</a>
                            <a class="btn btn-default" href="/downloads/send/19-latest/1248-keynote-address-by-mxolisi-mgojo-president-of-the-minerals-council-south-africa-at-joburg-indaba-2020" rel="external">Keynote address</a>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12 col-md-6 nopad-r">
                            <div class="row center-block">
                                <div class="col-xs-8 col-sm-5 col-md-6 nopad-r"><img src="/images/banners/joburg-indaba-speaker-baxter.png" alt="Roger Baxter [photo]" class="img-responsive center" /></div>
                                <div class="col-xs-8 col-sm-5 col-md-6 nopad-r"><img src="/images/banners/joburg-indaba-speaker-mgojo.png" alt="Mxolisi Mgojo [photo]" class="img-responsive center" /></div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <!--Masoyise-->
    <div class="item">
        <div class="row no-gutters b-mainpic banner-hm-masoyise-hp-seminar">
            <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12 col-md-9 col-lg-7 b-content pull-right">
                <div class="b-contentblock bc-green">
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12 col-md-12">
                            <h3 class="ib">Upcoming event: Masoyise workplace health virtual seminar</h3>
                            <p class="lead">Fighting the unrecognised pandemic: Reprioritising TB, HIV and NCDs in the era of COVID-19</p>
                            <p>
                                The Masoyise Health Programme is a multi-stakeholder initiative led by the Minerals Council to reduce the impact of TB, HIV, occupational lung diseases and non-communicable diseases as occupational health
                                threats in the mining sector.<br />
                                Join Minerals Council South Africa in discussion with Minister of Health, Dr Zweli Mkhize and experts from UNAIDS, ILO and the WHO as they share solutions to resolve this problem.
                            </p>
                            <p><a href="https://zoom.us/meeting/register/tJMlcu-sqzIjHdBHtcnG5-sM8XC2sW75oolt" target="blank">Register to attend</a> the seminar on 15 October 2020 at 11:00 – 14:00 CAT</p>
                            <h5>Speakers include:</h5>
                            <div class="row sml-90">
                                <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12 col-md-6 nopad-l">
                                    <p><strong>Dr Zweli Mkhize:</strong> Minister of Health, South Africa</p>
                                    <p><strong>Dr Shannon Hader:</strong> Deputy Executive Director UNAIDS</p>
                                    <p><strong>Dr Owen Kaluwa:</strong> WHO Representative to South Africa</p>
                                </div>
                                <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12 col-md-6">
                                    <p><strong>Ms Zanele Matlala:</strong> Vice President Minerals Council South Africa and Masoyise Health Programme Chair</p>
                                    <p><strong>Ms Alette van Leur:</strong> Director Sectoral Policies Department, ILO</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <a class="btn btn-default" href="/special-features/1163-masoyise-workplace-health-virtual-seminar" rel="external" title="Masoyise workplace health virtual seminar page">Read more</a>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <!--National Day of Women in Mining-->
    <div class="item">
        <div class="row no-gutters b-mainpic banner-hm-nd-women-mining-2020">
            <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12 col-md-4 col-lg-6 hero-block"></div>
